# Cardiovascular Disease Prediction using Machine Learning

A comprehensive web-based system for predicting cardiovascular disease risk using advanced machine learning techniques.

## Key Features
- Data preprocessing and feature engineering
- Implementation of multiple ML algorithms (Random Forest, Decision Tree, Logistic Regression, SVM)
- Model performance evaluation and comparison
- Feature importance analysis using LIME
- Web interface for user input and risk prediction

## Tech Stack
- Python (NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn)
- Flask for web framework
- HTML/CSS for frontend

## Highlights
- Achieved 94% accuracy with Random Forest algorithm
- Implements feature selection for improved model performance
- Provides interpretable results with risk percentage and contributing factors


This project aims to assist in early detection and risk assessment of cardiovascular diseases, potentially improving patient outcomes through timely intervention.
